HEADWORD: Dogshore
<hw>Dog"shore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>One of several shores used to hold a ship firmly and prevent her
moving while the blocks are knocked away before launching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dogsick</ent>⟦br⟧
